TY  - JOUR
AB  - This paper analyzes the effects of stochastic taxes on production in a simple stochastic growth model. In so doing, the paper explicitly examines the importance of uncertainty on the decisions of individual agents. This importance is emphasized by comparing economic outcomes to various realizations of tax rates under uncertainty and perfect foresight.
